  • Classes in tiles used by tiles 
    Class and Description
    BuildingEnum
    The BuildingEnum represents each Building and stores their appropriate image and textual representation
    BuildingTile
    BuildingTile is a layer of the Tile that stores the Building as a BuildingEnum
    GroundEnum
    The GroundEnum stores each type of regular ground a Tile can have, as well as its graphical and textual representation.
    GroundTile
    The GroundTile represents the layer in a Tile that determines things like movement.
    ResourceEnum
    The ResourceEnum stores the different possible resources on a Tile.
    ResourceTile
    The ResourceTile represents the layer of a Tile that holds resources.
    Tile
    Tile represents each individual cell of the Map.
    TileWrapper
    TileWrapper represents each possible layer of a Tile.
    WeatherEnum
    The WeatherEnum represents the possible weather for the WeatherTile layer of a Tile.
    WeatherTile
    WeatherTile represents the layer of a Tile that has weather, such as day or a storm.
